rate:
'RATED
  I ordered from the Navratra Menu during Navratri this month. Out of the wide variety offered I ordered the Sabudana Vada and Curd meal and Kuttu Aloo Parantha with Paneer Makhanwala Royal Meal.

The Sabudana Vada was perfectly made and was a great light meal paired with curd. The Kutti Aloo Paratha and Paneer Makhanwala Royal Meal was a great combination. Making aloo paratha with Kuttu is a great idea and it tasted amazing. The meal also included a portion of curd and a portion of Hare Tamatar ki Sabzi.

The overall experience of ordering food from here was excellent as the food was delivered fresh and on time with good packing to avoid spills and leaks.

name:
""RATED
  The place made me come back to write a review after a long time..

A place with a different ambience.
Moment I saw it reminded me of exams in school days.

We tried the starter - school captain.
The soft chicken and the thick gravy of onion paste was really nice. With right amount of spices n spring onions n chillies.

Double chocolate shake was my favourite drink compared to peanut butter and strawberry shake. While ordering the peanut butter and strawberry shake we were so very skeptical thinking how's this gonna blend together. It was nice except the cream topping. More of peanut butter taste than the strawberry.

And coming to the double decker beef burger was little dissappointed since it didn't look even close to the photos in menu card. And the beef patty was overloaded with a flavored leave. It completely missed the fresh lettuce leaves. Still I would say the burger is above 3.5/5

Overall a great place to be. Loved the food and ambience. Pricing is reasonable."")
rate: the staff is friendly too and their service is also pretty fast !\nOverall a great place !')

cuisines:
'RATED
  This is an interesting little theme based restaurant near Ulsoor lake. Very well located on the main road.

Ambience: Chuck and piggy felt right at home as you can see from the pictures. The school theme was well executed across all the different aspects of the place. From the menu to the water bottles and cutlery holder. Even the noodles came in a open tiffin box.

Food: the menu had a wide mix of foods available from sandwiches
approx_cost(for two people): burgers
listed_in(type):
'RATED
  I always love themed restaurants which was the reason to visit this restaurant. I could see the effort they had put to make the school memories come alive. It had a lot of unique elements which indeed made this restaurant special than others.

We got complementary ice cubes which made me feel even happier. We had Summer squash which smelled little weird upon complaining the staff took back the order. Potato head and salt & pepper mushroom was average in taste. The staff was welcoming.

Overall I would suggest you visit if you want to relive school days.')
